The paper discusses the optimization of deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the visualization and analysis of the loss landscape during training, which is a key aspect of optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these fields heavily rely on deep learning and optimization. Additionally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also possible sub-categories, as they are related to the optimization and analysis of neural networks.
